        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 1:31AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 130 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Snyder, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dunn, Colorado City Airport, Hermleigh, Randalls Corner, J B Thomas
Reservoir, Ira, Winston Field, Knapp, Cuthbert, and Snyder.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 211 and 212.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
